THE ALEX JONES SHOW
2009.05.19 Tuesday

Alex welcomes back to the show Charlie Skelton, the Guardian journalist harassed, tailed and surveyed by plain-clothes cops, and twice arrested by Greek police as he covered the Bilderberg meeting. Alex also talks with economist and author John Perkins. Perkins says that he &quot;was an 'economic hit man' for 10 years, helping U.S. intelligence agencies and multinational corporations cajole and blackmail foreign leaders into serving U.S. foreign policy and awarding lucrative contracts to American business. Perkins writes about his experiences in his book, Confessions of an Economic Hit Man. Alex also covers the news of 

the day and takes your calls. 

HR 1: News &amp; review, open lines, spying, carbon tax, development of society
HR 2: JOHN PERKINS  - confessions of an economic hitman
HR 3: John Perkins w/calls, news, PAUL WATSON
HR 4: Open lines, CHARLEY SKELTON, military call from Iraq, vet call


